File: Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane. JOHANNESBURG - National Assembly Speaker, Thandi Modise has appointed a panel to assess Public Protector, Busisiwe Mkhwebane's fitness to hold office. The panel includes retired Constitutional Court Judge Bess Nkabinde, senior counsel Dumisa Ntsebeza, and Johan de Waal. The motion to remove Mkhwebane from her role as public protector was tabled by DA chief whip, Natasha Mazzone earlier this year. READ: Committee asked to look into Mkhwebane's fitness for office But Mkhwebane is challenging her removal in court. The first part of her case was dismissed by the Western Cape High Court last month. The court heard her application for leave to appeal the decision earlier this week before it reserved judgment.